TOKYO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks opened sharply higher Thursday, with the benchmark Nikkei index gaining over 3 percent, as market confidence was boosted by advances on Wall Street following an optimistic outlook for the U.S. economy presented by Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell. After the market opened here, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average increased 827.52 points, or 3.21 percent, from Wednesday to 26,589.53. The broader Topix index of all First Section issues on the Tokyo Stock Exchange gained 45.49 points, or 2.45 percent, to reach 1,898.74. Gainers were led by electric appliance, precision instrument, and machinery issues.  â– 